      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be demonstrated as the clinically relevant metric and directly linked to the device acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "NIH is used as primary QoI and is consistent with ISO 10993-4 guidance; however, the mapping from NIH to patient-level hemoglobin release rate has not been formally documented in the submission package. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
